io.github.samwright.framework.model

Interface Element

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ChildOf<Workflow>, Controllable, Deletable, EventuallyImmutable, Processor, Replaceable, Validatable, Versioned, XMLSerialisable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    TopProcessor, WorkflowContainer
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractElement, AbstractWorkflowContainer, Adder, ChooserWorkflowContainer, ContourFinder, ExContainer, FingertipFinder, FingertipReducer, HandDetector, ImageLoader, KeyboardActor, MockElement, NNClassifier, Optimiser, PalmDetector, SimplifyContour, SkinDetector, SplitJoinWorkflowContainer, StartElement, StaticColourRange, TopWorkflowContainer, Viewer

    public interface Element
extends Processor, ChildOf<Workflow>
    An Element is a Processor which sits inside a Workflow. It can be observed by ElementObserver objects, which are registered with the withObservers(newObservers) method.

        Return a version of this with the given parent.
